# Enforce LF line endings in-tree on every platform.
#
# Why: the byte-identity gates (e.g. tests/fixture-pipeline.test.js) compare a
# committed golden read with fs.readFileSync(..., "utf8") against JSON.stringify
# output, which is always LF. On Windows, git's core.autocrlf=true otherwise
# checks the golden out as CRLF, so every line "differs" by a trailing \r and the
# test fails locally while passing on CI (Linux). eol=lf keeps the working tree LF
# so Windows and CI agree. The committed blobs are already LF — this changes no
# stored content, only how files are written to the working tree on checkout.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets: never apply text/eol conversion or line-diffing.
*.wav binary
*.ttf binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.webp binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.pdf binary
